title: The reactions N-14(n,alpha)B-11 and N-14(n,t)C-12 observed with a gridded ionization chamber

x4freetext: Institut fur Experimental Physik.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zeitschrift fuer Physik, Vol.197, p.124 (1966)

x4freetext: The reactions N-14(n,alpha)B-11 and N-14(n,t)C-12
observed with a gridded ionization chamber
Van de Graaff generator used between
1.1 MeV and 3.3 MeV.
Small 150 kV generator used to calibrate
flux by providing a source with very low gamma
background.
Deuterium gas target. Neutrons produced with
energies between 4.0 MeV and 6.4 MeV at 0 deg.
.Ionization chamber gas also used as sample.
.Direct detection of emitted alphas.
Gridded ionization chamber filled with argon-
nitrogen mixture placed at 0 degrees to the
deuteron beam 50 cm from the gas cell.
Long counter positioned 4.6 m behind the gas
target in the beam direction, and-
two organic scintillators were used to monitor
the neutron flux.
Flux determined as a two stage process-
1.The cross section for N-14(n,alpha0) was measured at
a neutron angle corresponding to 2.48 MeV neutrons.
2.The same cross section was the measured on the low
gamma-background. Small accelerator relative to the
Li-6(n,t) cross section at  2.48 MeV (determined
with a Li-I(Eu) crystal enriched in Li-6 in the
target position).

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Brookhaven National Laboratory report series, No.325 (1964)

Graphs given in this work, tabulated values
taken from Bormann(CCDN11 680326 10).
.Two main corrections-
1.loss of efficiency as a result of particles
striking the counter walls.
2.Neutron flux corrections, composed of-
attenuation of neutrons in Ionization chamber
before reaching the long counter.
Efficiency of long counter at various energies.
Different solid angles subtended by Ionization
chamber and long counter at the neutron source.
Total error consists of partial errors in the
relative measurement of-
long counter counting corrections (each).3.0%
position and size of sensitive volume... 3.0%
wall loss correction (upper limit).. 5.0%
statistical error (upper limit)..... 1.0%
Error in the absolute measurement of 8% in
the Li-6(n,alpha) cross section at 2.48 MeV and in its
measurement in this work.
Cross sections are threfore accurate to about-
15 to 20% for (n,alpha0)
30% for (n,alpha1)
30% for (n,triton0)
